@startuml
title mHealth Tympanometer - Screen State Machine

' --- styling ---
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam ranksep 55
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #F6F6F6
  BorderColor #444444
  FontColor #111111
  ArrowColor #555555
  ArrowFontColor #333333
}
hide empty description

' --- states ---
state "1 - Boot / Self-test"       as Boot
state "2 - Ready"                  as Ready
state "3 - Seeking Seal"           as Seal
state "4 - Measuring (screen OFF)" as Meas
state "5 - Results"                as Results
state "6 - Re-arm"                 as Rearm
state "7 - Session Summary"        as Summary
state "8 - Warning"                as Warn
state "9 - Error (fatal)"          as Error
state "10 - Sleep / Dim"           as Sleep

' --- main vertical happy path (top -> bottom) ---
[*]     -down->  Boot
Boot    -down->  Ready    : all interfaces OK
Ready   -down->  Seal     : trigger press
Seal    -down->  Meas     : seal >= 20 daPa
Meas    -down->  Results  : sweep done
Results -down->  Rearm    : auto-delay / trigger
Rearm   -down->  Summary  : both ears done
Summary -left->  Ready    : next patient
Rearm   -left->  Seal     : other ear pending

' --- side branches (kept off the spine) ---
Boot    -right-> Error    : interface fails
Error   -up->    Boot     : button restarts
Ready   -right-> Sleep    : 5 min idle
Sleep   -up->    Ready    : button press
Seal    -right-> Warn     : seal timeout 5 s
Meas    -right-> Warn     : pressure-inc timeout
Warn    -left->  Ready    : aborts (ble_tx -> idle)

' --- notes (single-line to avoid widening the graph) ---
note right of Meas : Screen OFF; safety LED pulses.\nKeeps OLED charge-pump noise off the mic.
note left of Results : Curve pinned. Stat cell auto-pages\nType / Conf / ECV / SA / TPP every 2-3 s.

@enduml
